§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We extend modular arithmetic to the real numbers. ⦉
⦉

§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Two real numbers $x, y ∈ 𝗥$ are congruent modulo $α ∈ 𝗥$
    if their difference is a multiple of $α$ ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ For $x, y ∈ 𝗥$, if $x$ and $y$ are congruent modulo $α ∈
    𝗥$ we write
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ x ≡ y (\mod α) ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

